Saudi Arabia Has No Reason to Alter Currency Peg, Al-Jasser Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-10-08T18:46:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-08/saudi-arabia-has-no-reason-to-alter-currency-peg-al-jasser-says.html
Saudi Arabia , the Arab world’s
biggest economy, has no reason to change its policy of pegging
the riyal to the dollar, the kingdom’s central bank Governor
Muhammad al-Jasser told reporters in  Riyadh  today.  Inflation in Saudi Arabia is stable and set to drop, al-
Jasser said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
C. Thompson at 
 cthompson1@bloomberg.net  